e correlation function $f(r_{12})$ needs to diverge\nfor large $r_{12}$ at large internuclear distances while for shorter bond\ndistances it increases as a function of $r_{12}$ to a maximum value after which\nit decays exponentially. We further give a physical interpretation of this\nbehavior.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Jan 2014 17:51:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Mar 2014 07:36:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 12 May 2014 15:00:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-05-13"}
